===Etymology===
From Nahuatl ''[[popoloca]]'' "speak unintelligibly".

===Proper noun===
'''Popoloca'''

#A name for several different indigenous languages of Mexico, including languages of the [[Mixe-Zoquean]] family and the [[Oto-Manguean]] family.

